<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>PvP - Alot of fun: It will suprise some people..</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Geiger">Geiger</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:26 a.m. 21/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> PvP - Alot of fun: It will suprise some people..<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>My roomate has been playing EQ for like 12 - 16 hours a day (with the exception of only a couple days) since phase 4 started. His played time yesterday early was well over 5 days. He didn't play much differently when it was the non PvP server of 3.5. He hadn't been much into playing PvP because the play just wasn't there in 3.5. Since 4.0 however I've seen him having a much more enjoyable time in EQ. Taking his time to make lvls but also taking stretches out to chase Dark Elves and other baddies down. Its amazing how much more depth the game seems to have with the PvP turned on. Thing's aren't getting too far out of hand either, you can get away from people fairly easy, so its alot of tactics involved with PvPing with people. It has turned out to be alot of fun without the feeling of the UO Pkers. 2 Highest LvLs on the PvP server are lvl 17 Stoneman and Rezzak.

<P>Geiger
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
